<bibRefCitation author="Judkins, D. C." box="[668,820,1804,1827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref4646" refString="Judkins, D. C. (1978) Pelagic shrimps of the Sergestes edwardsii species group (Crustacea: Decapoda: Sergestidae). Smithsonian Contrbution of Zoology, 256, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="1978">Judkins, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Adult male: A—petasma (left), dorsal; Ip, pb; pu; pe; pm; sh; pv; la; lac; lc; lt; li; pa; B—petasma (right), dorsal; Ip; pb; pu; pe; pm; sh, sheath; pv; la; lac; lc; lt; li; pa; C—left appendix masculina.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1322,284,390]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Appendix masculina single (
<figureCitation box="[665,761,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[264,367,1804,1828]" captionTargetBox="[353,1220,607,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-140@6.[340,1247,592,1786]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sergestes brevispinatus, Judkins, 1978. Adult male: A—petasma (left), dorsal; Ip, pb; pu; pe; pm; sh; pv; la; lac; lc; lt; li; pa; B—petasma (right), dorsal; Ip; pb; pu; pe; pm; sh, sheath; pv; la; lac; lc; lt; li; pa; C—left appendix masculina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051226/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) paddle­shaped lobe bearing spines on distal margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1322,284,390]" box="[312,1167,364,390]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Thelycum of female (
<figureCitation box="[565,657,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[264,368,1107,1131]" captionTargetBox="[350,1233,439,1081]" captionTargetId="figure-225@7.[340,1247,428,1096]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Sergestes brevispinatus Judkins, 1978. Adult female: A—exterior sexual organ, ventral; thelycum and coxae of third pereiopods, postero­ventral view; op; ap; gc; pxp; mp; pp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051230/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
) with third coxa and sixth thoracic sternite.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051230" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5051230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051230/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" startId="7.[264,368,1107,1131]" targetBox="[350,1233,439,1081]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1323,1107,1167]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,399,1107,1131]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Judkins, 1978" authorityName=", Judkins" authorityYear="1978" box="[411,844,1107,1130]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Sergestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevispinatus">
<emphasis box="[411,678,1107,1130]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Sergestes brevispinatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Judkins, D. C." box="[688,844,1107,1130]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref4646" refString="Judkins, D. C. (1978) Pelagic shrimps of the Sergestes edwardsii species group (Crustacea: Decapoda: Sergestidae). Smithsonian Contrbution of Zoology, 256, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="1978">Judkins, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Adult female: A—exterior sexual organ, ventral; thelycum and coxae of third pereiopods, postero­ventral view; op; ap; gc; pxp; mp; pp.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1320,1222,1448]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Sixth thoracic sternite anteriorly forming operculum (OP) projecting posteriorly over common slit­like aperture of sperm receptacles; posterior half of sternite with low transverse ridge terminating beneath proximal projections (PP) on coxa in two low, anteriorly directed sternal protuberances (PB) and with shallow groove extending along midline between transverse ridge and receptacle aperture. Genital cavity (GC) relatively narrow in ventral view, extending distally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1321,1502,1608]" box="[264,407,1502,1527]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[264,407,1502,1527]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1321,1502,1608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Judkins" authorityYear="1978" box="[312,587,1542,1567]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Sergestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevispinatus">
<emphasis box="[312,587,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Sergestes brevispinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. appears to prefer oceanic waters close to continental margin of Central and South America, eastern tropical Pacific and now from Indian Ocean.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1324,1662,1888]" box="[264,366,1662,1687]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[264,366,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1324,1662,1888]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Judkins, D. C." box="[473,648,1702,1728]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref4646" refString="Judkins, D. C. (1978) Pelagic shrimps of the Sergestes edwardsii species group (Crustacea: Decapoda: Sergestidae). Smithsonian Contrbution of Zoology, 256, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="1978">Judkins (1978)</bibRefCitation>
the shortness of the outer distal and outer terminal spines on the maxilliped third dactylus and are relatively similar spines in present specimens. Whereas petasma of male of Judkins processus ventralis (PV), lobus armatus (LA) and lobus connectens (LC) are very prominent but in present specimen processus ventralis (PV) is totally absent. Lobus armatus (LA) thin and lobus connectens (LC) very reduced.
</paragraph>
